<br>
Here's how to do it.<br>
<br>
1) Buy some Ant's potion in the Bazaar first, so you can shrink yourself.  I buy a 10 dose.<br>
<br>
2) Go to Ak`Anon and find the Southernmost building in the lake (near PoD).  This is the castle.  Go inside to the first 4-way and head East.  Go down a ramp, and poke around.  You'll find the King down yet another ramp and off to the &quot;right&quot; in an adjacent room as you're going down the ramp.<br>
<br>
3) Shrink.  Summon Fluffy and keep him at the bottom of the ramp.  You can shrink him if you want to.<br>
<br>
4) Pull Gnomie with an annul.  Stand on the ramp just above your pet a bit.  I say &quot;above&quot; because the pet is at the floor level, while you've climbed a tad of elevation due to the ramp.  He'll putz around a bit trying to figure the right path.  He may cast on you some.  Ignore it.  <br>
<br>
5) Keep pet quiet, while King is trying to find you.  I use hold.  Not really necessary, though.  King will either pop just behind you (up a bit higher on the ramp) or will attack you by coming 'round the &quot;door&quot; near the bottom.  Either way, make sure he's in front of your pet; that is, ensure he's in a position where the pet will push him UP the ramp, before you tell pet to attack.<br>
<br>
6) Pet attack.  Heal him some.  I usually get the King up to the top pinned in the corner, then mosey up past him in the corner with the watchmen, and blast him.  He summons sometimes, so be aware of that.<br>
<br>
Pretty fun fight.  32k HP.  Let your DS do its work, and malosini him.  There seem to be a couple different forms of him.  One likes to melee a ton, and the other likes to cast a lot.  Whoever said bury your KEI is right, heh.  I end up with 40 to 80 percent mana at the end of the fight, depending on whether I have host up, and what mood I'm in. =)<br>
<br>
Nice XP for when you can't find a group, or if you're just grumpy and don't want to deal with people.<br>
<br>
